Introduction

AMBITION is a five-member independent boy group. They are actively promoting in Japan and have plans to debut in South Korea.

The group announced their plans to debut in Japan on March 15, 2022, when they revealed their performance at ShowBox in Tokyo. They later confirmed that they would also hold a pre-debut concert at the same venue in December, before officially launching their Japanese career.

On January 24, 2024, their company announced that Taeho left the group for personal reasons.
